Branding expert Andy Rice critiques the Economic Freedom Fighters’ (EFF) brand, delving into its image, election manifesto and its social media presence. JOHANNESBURG - Every week The Money Show’s Bruce Whitfield asks branding and advertising expert Andy Rice to share with him the week’s advertising 'heroes' and/or 'zeroes'. This week, with general elections around the corner, Rice critiqued the Economic Freedom Fighters’ (EFF) brand. "A brand is not just a promise made, but a promise kept as well… Many things in their manifesto seem utterly unachievable… "They have a simple, memorable theme slogan, just five words: ‘Our land and jobs now’. "In terms of followers on Twitter; they’re substantially larger than the ANC… They understand the power of personality." Listen to the audio above for more. 